Description:
    Generates a Rails migration with the appropriate database columns for Strata attributes.
    This generator maps each Strata attribute type to its required database columns automatically.
    Additionally, it supports all standard Rails migration types.

Usage:
    bin/rails generate strata:migration NAME [attribute:type attribute:type] [options]

Examples:
    bin/rails generate strata:migration AddPersonalInfoToUsers name:name date_of_birth:memorable_date
    bin/rails generate strata:migration AddAddressesToApplications home_address:address work_address:address
    bin/rails generate strata:migration AddFinancialInfoToReports salary:money tax_id:tax_id
    bin/rails generate strata:migration AddPeriodicsToProfile leave_periods:array reporting_periods:array

Supported Attribute Types:
    address              - Creates columns: street_line_1, street_line_2, city, state, zip_code (all :string)
    array                - Creates columns: single :jsonb column for storing arrays of objects
    date_range           - Creates columns: start, end (both :date)
    memorable_date       - Creates columns: single :date column
    money                - Creates columns: single :integer column (stores cents)
    name                 - Creates columns: first, middle, last (all :string)
    tax_id               - Creates columns: single :string column
    us_date              - Creates columns: single :date column
    year_month           - Creates columns: year (:integer), month (:integer)
    year_quarter         - Creates columns: year (:integer), quarter (:integer)
    year_quarter_range   - Creates columns: start_year, start_quarter, end_year, end_quarter (all :integer)
    standard Rails types - Any additional standard Rails migration types can be specified as needed.

This will create:
    A standard Rails migration file with the appropriate column definitions for each Strata attribute type, as well as any standard Rails migration types.
